Compiling
---------

Compiling and jar-ing the software is done with Jakarta's 
Ant (http://jakarta.apache.org/ant/):

cdk/$ ls build.xml
build.xml
cdk/$ ant

Running tests
-------------

After you compiled the code:

cdk/$ cd build
cdk/build/$ java -cp .:../jar/cml-2.0.jar:../jar/xerces-1.3.0.jar:../jar/cml-2.0.jar:../jar/junit.jar:../jar/vecmath1.1-1.12.jar \
org.openscience.cdk.test.FileReaderTest

The avaiable tests are:

org.openscience.cdk.test.FileReaderTest		Reads an MDL Molfile, XYZ or CML file
org.openscience.cdk.test.ControllerTest		Reads and edit a file
org.openscience.cdk.test.CDKTests		Tests automatic drawing of structures
org.openscience.cdk.test.DatabaseTest		Read a structure from a JDBC compliant database

